Sugar Prices May Fall Next Week on Brazil Output, Survey Says

-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m   a n d   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-07-14T23:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/sugar-prices-may-fall-next-week-on-brazil-output-survey-says.html
Sugar may decline next week on signs
production in  Brazil , the world’s largest exporter, will be
bigger than some analysts expected.  Seven of eight traders, analysts and brokers surveyed by
Bloomberg News said raw sugar in New York would decline. One was
neutral. Before today, futures for October delivery dropped 1.2
percent this week to 29.02 cents a pound on ICE Futures U.S.  Six respondents said refined sugar on  London ’s NYSE Liffe
would fall, while two were neutral. Futures for October delivery
gained 2.2 percent this week through yesterday.  Three respondents said refined sugar’s premium over raw may
narrow, three were neutral, and two said it would widen.  -- Editors: Daniel Enoch, Millie Munshi.  To contact the reporters on this story:
